Marcus,

Congratulations on your degree and thank you for attending Wallace State.  We are sorry to learn that you didn’t have a better experience. Mechatronics is one of our most popular applied technology programs with strong industry partnerships, apprenticeship opportunities, outstanding job placement rates, and national accreditation. Please know that our Career Services office remains available to alumni after graduation and can assist you with job search, resume preparation, and interview skills. We hope you will reach out to us at wallacecares@wallacestate.edu if we can help further.

Best wishes,
Wallace State Community College

name: Ashlee Uhlar
text:
Great school, received my Associates and transferred afterwards to UAH.  Really sweet people.  If you live far away be prepared to only communicate in-person for Financial Aid and Admissions.  It's very difficult to reach people by phone or email but once you walk in (unless it's right before the semester starts) there is usually no line and a short wait to talk to the right people.    
Also, this school is known for its nursing program and they take great pride in that.  Be aware that the course load for this major is at university-level (minimum).  Seriously, it is very aggressive but the job placement and license pass-rates are stellar.  
I enjoyed the faculty at this campus, especially in math.  I took business classes too, and most of those instructors were super friendly and easy to follow.
Best of luck to your future education, this is not the easiest community college but I think it is absolutely worth it!  :)

name: Justin Bzdell
text:
Hello,
I highly suggest Calhoun Community College to any High School Senior who is about to take the next step into college. If you are one of those people like me that is paying for school with Student Loans, but doesn't want to much debt when they leave school. Then I highly suggest Calhoun Community College. Calhoun is only $139 a credit hour compared to UAH $424 (something like that) but not giving up on a good education, then Calhoun is for you.

I absolutely love the professors I have had, and how much future and potential the school has with all the new buildings at the Huntsville Campus. I really like how Calhoun dominates every other Community College in the state of Alabama (it really showed at the Leadership Convention). I talked to A LOT of students from other Community College's state wide and were so jealous of all the different class times and variety of different types of classes that they didn't have at their schools.

Thanks!
Justin Bzdell
